# Movement Analytics Context

## Project Name & Purpose
- **Project:** Movement Analytics
- **Purpose:** Analyze user-uploaded squat videos and return practical movement-quality feedback (scores, observations, coaching cues) from computer-vision-derived frames plus AI interpretation.
- **Positioning:** Premium sports-tech coaching feedback; not medical diagnosis.

## Complete Tech Stack
- **Framework:** Next.js App Router (`next@16`), React 19
- **Language:** TypeScript
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS v4 + design tokens in `app/globals.css`
- **Auth / DB / Storage:** Supabase (`@supabase/supabase-js`, `@supabase/ssr`)
- **AI:** Anthropic SDK (`@anthropic-ai/sdk`)
- **Frame extraction:** External Railway service via HTTP (`FRAMES_SERVICE_URL`)

## Styling Conventions
- Use global token variables from `app/globals.css` (`--bg-page`, `--bg-card`, `--text-*`, `--accent`, `--border`, `--score-*`, `--shadow-card`).
- Keep landing marketing section (`components/landing/Hero.tsx`) dramatic dark HUD style.
- Keep product pages (analyze, processing, results, dashboard, auth) in the light Apple-style system.
- Prefer tokenized color usage (`text-[var(--text-primary)]`) over hardcoded values in product UI.

## API Integrations & Environment Variables
- Required app env vars:
  - `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`
  - `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`
  - `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`
  - `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`
  - `FRAMES_SERVICE_URL`
  - `FRAMES_SERVICE_SECRET`
- Supabase auth session refresh is handled in `middleware.ts`.
- Auth callback route: `app/auth/callback/route.ts`.
- Analysis pipeline route: `app/api/analyze/route.ts`.

## Coding Conventions
- TypeScript-first. Keep explicit request/response typing in API routes.
- Server/client split:
  - Browser Supabase client: `lib/supabase/client.ts`
  - Server Supabase client: `lib/supabase/server.ts`
- Keep AI parsing defensive and normalize persisted rows before UI consumption.
- Keep presentational UI in `components/`, business/data logic in `lib/`.
- Preserve API JSON contracts and `SquatAnalysisResult` shape stability.

## Things To Never Do
- Never log full secrets or credentials.
- Never use medical diagnosis language in prompts or user-facing copy.
- Never remove auth cookie propagation for protected client->API calls (`credentials: "include"` where needed).
- Never break the core flow contract: upload -> processing -> status/progress -> results.
- Never introduce broad multi-movement abstractions unless explicitly requested.
